04625nam a22005655i 9780773594784DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20112011xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735947847 a10.1515/97807735947842doi  a(DE-B1597)658096  a(OCoLC)1394872577  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aBF51b.H2513 2013eb 7aPHI0000002bisacsh04a200.9/042231 aHakl, Hans Thomas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aEranos :bAn Alternative Intellectual History of the Twentieth Century /cHans Thomas Hakl. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[2011] 4c©2011  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tPreface and Acknowledgments -- tIntroduction: How This Book Emerged -- tThe Significance of Eranos -- tAn Esoteric Prelude to Eranos -- tYearning for the East: Monte Verità and the School of Wisdom -- tToward Eranos -- tThe First Eranos Meeting: An Idea Comes to Life -- tEranos and National Socialism -- tThe Years 1934–37 -- tEranos 1938: The United States Shows Interest -- tThe War Years -- tNew Prospects after the World Conflict -- tThe Heyday Begins -- tThe Early 1950s -- tPolytheism Versus Monotheism -- tAn End, Some New Beginnings, and Repeated Turbulence -- tDelicate Questions and Attempts to Answer Them -- tEranos as a Prototype -- tThe End of a Cycle & or Perhaps Not -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFrom 1933 and for a period of almost seventy years, Italy's Lake Maggiore region was the gathering place for some of the world's foremost philosophers. Once a year, illustrious thinkers such as Carl Jung, Erich Neumann, Mircea Eliade, D.T. Suzuki, and Adolph Pormann gathered there for Eranos - a meeting of the minds for elite intellectuals. Hans Hakl presents the only complete study of what is arguably the single most important gathering of scholars in the twentieth century. Eranos chronicles the golden years of Jung, Corbin, Eliade, and Scholem, tracing the roots of the Ascona movement in Theosophy, its later branches, and many lesser-known but no less fascinating figures. Distilling decades of archival research and interviews with Eranos participants, Hakl illuminates the trialogue of religion, esotericism, and scholarship that began with Eranos and continues to the present day. This finely crafted history shows how Eranos played an important counterpart to the dominant spiritual and intellectual history of the twentieth century by encouraging freedom of thought and radicality. Detailing the development and influence of a movement that set the course of contemporary philosophical thought, Eranos is a landmark volume that will draw readers interested in the history of ideas, psychology, religious and cultural studies, Jewish and Islamic studies, the history of science, mysticism, and the development of new age religions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIntellectual lifexHistoryy20th century. 0aOccultismxHistoryy20th century. 0aPsychology and religionxHistoryy20th century. 0aReligionxHistoryy20th century. 0aSpiritualism (Philosophy)xHistoryy20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359478440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773594784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773594784/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9 